Implement the private `select/3` function used by `FeatureFlags` to resolve a
deterministic bucket to a variant name.

`select/3` takes three arguments:

1. a list of `{variant_name, weight}` tuples in the order the variants were
   declared,
2. `bucket` â€” a `0..99` integer produced by `:erlang.phash2({flag, user}, 100)`,
   and
3. `acc` â€” the running sum of the weights already consumed (callers pass `0`).

It walks the variant list in order, accumulating weights, so that variant 1 owns
buckets `0..w1-1`, variant 2 owns `w1..w1+w2-1`, and so on. For the head
`{name, weight}`, compute the exclusive upper edge of that variant's range as
`acc + weight`. If `bucket` falls below that upper edge, the bucket belongs to
this variant, so return `name`; otherwise recurse into the rest of the list with
the accumulator advanced to the new upper edge.

A variant with weight `0` therefore owns an empty range and can never be
selected. If the list is exhausted without matching (which should not happen when
weights sum to 100, but guards against malformed input), return `:off`.

